title: For Sale:  Handgun ammo
postcontent: Hello everyone. I am always shopping around for ammo. I always seem to go everywhere and always find what I don't need. I have recently noticed all the ammo price gouging going on here. So because of that reason I have decided to begin posting the location of any bulk ammo that I find in retail stores. As of now I am located in the mint Hill area and have been shopping at local retail locations. The Walmart on Albemarle Road seems to have handgun ammunition but they are always out of Winchester and Remington 9 mm and 380. They always seem to have the most handgun ammunition available. Through talking to sales associates at Walmart I have come to find out that they get trucks every other night. Freight comes out on the floor at 9 o'clock but you should check with gun sales department to see what time associates leave at night. Sometimes you only have an hour window to get ammunition because no one is left in the department with keys. Also Dick's sporting goods in Matthews has been getting trucks on Friday morning. According to Lodge associate they have been getting more ammunition than normal. But they have been setting a limit on ammunition purchases. He also said that they have been getting in .223. Don't bother going to the Walmart in Indian Trail. As of yesterday they only had a few boxes of miscellaneous ammunition nothing for handguns. Also Walmart in locust has been out all handgun ammunition. I have occasionally seen 22 WinMag there. Information pertaining to when freight comes out on the floor at Walmart was acquired at Locust Walmart not sure if that pertains to the other store locations. Also Dick's sporting goods used to offer 10% off with case purchase you may be able to sneak that deal in with some sales associates. Look for cases of shotgun ammo with an orange sticker. I will continue to post any information about ammunition as I come across that. I hope this helps others out and saves them money. Good luck.
